{
  "texts": [
    "Indeed, algorithms are able to more accurately predict Openness and Extraversion from people's Facebook status updates than Conscientiousness and Agreeableness 71.",
    "In contrast, the consistent null effect that was observed for AI-generated messages matched to participants' level of Agreeableness might be explained by the association of the trait with a broad susceptibility to persuasion 72.",
    "That is, people who are higher in Agreeableness are more likely to respond to persuasive content than those lower in Agreeableness, regardless of the specific personalization strategy deployed.",
    "Future research should establish whether these differences are unique to the LLM-generated content, or whether theoretical factors do indeed underlie them (i.e., they would emerge in human-generated content, too).",
    "For example, some research suggests that Agreeableness is associated with altruism and harmony in social relationships 73, which none of our AI-generated messages referenced."
  ]
}